A vintage 1960s-style illustration of a grand medieval castle gate with an ornate iron portcullis partially lowered, viewed from inside looking out. Through the bars, shadowy silhouettes of figures stand waiting, unable to enter. A regal guard in ceremonial armor stands beside a large leather-bound ledger on a wooden podium, running a finger down a list while shaking his head. The scene uses warm sepia tones with rich burgundy and gold accents, featuring cross-hatched shading and slightly faded edges reminiscent of old book illustrations. Dramatic torchlight casts long shadows across cobblestone floors, creating a sense of selective exclusion and gatekeeping.
